BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee 
of the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] sent a message of greetings 
to the third congress of the Panhellenic Socialist Movement on 
April 13. 
  The message expressed the belief that the third congress 
would be conducive to strengthening and developing the 
Panhellenic Socialist Movement for peace and security, 
independent development and prosperity of the country and social 
progress. 
  "We believe that the friendly and cooperative relations 
between the two parties will develop favourably in the idea of 
independence, peace and friendship," it said. 

